<div class="syntax_wiki">
<p>You can use wiki syntax in your message:</p>
<ul>
    <li class="wiki-image source"><strong>source code bloc</strong>: the bloc should be surrounded by &lt;code&gt; and &lt;/code&gt;</li>
    <li class="wiki-image list"><strong>List</strong>: each line should begin by one or several *, - or #</li>
    <li class="wiki-image quote"><strong>blockquote</strong>: each line should begin by one or several ></li>
    <li class="wiki-image bold"><strong>bold</strong>: <strong>__text__</strong> (2 underscores)</li>
    <li class="wiki-image italic"><strong>italic</strong>: <em>''text''</em> (2 quotes)</li>
    <li class="wiki-image link"><strong>Link</strong>: [[ link name | link url ]] or [[ link url ]]</li>
</ul>
<p>Advanced wiki syntax</p>
<ul>
    <li class="wiki-image para"><strong>Paragraphe</strong>: 2 break line</li>
    <li class="wiki-image def"><strong>Definitions</strong>: ;term : definition + a break line</li>
</ul>
<p>Inside sentences:</p>
<ul>
    <li class="wiki-image full_link"><strong>Full link</strong>: [[link name|link url|lang|title]]</li>
    <li class="wiki-image carriage_return"><strong>Forced break line</strong>: %%%</li>
    <li class="wiki-image image"><strong>Image</strong>: ((image link|alternative text | position |description)). position: l/L/g/G => left, r/R/d/D =>right, nothing=>inline.</li>
    <li class="wiki-image code"><strong>code</strong> : @@code@@</li>
    <li class="wiki-image quoting"><strong>cite</strong> : ^^sentence|lang|link of source^^</li>
    <li class="wiki-image ref"><strong>reference (cite)</strong> : {literal}{{reference}}{/literal}</li>
    <li class="wiki-image acronym"><strong>acronym</strong> : ??acronym|explanation??</li>
</ul>
</div>